      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Views on school lessons about gender identity vary widely because they touch on values regarding biological reality, social development, and family upbringing. One common viewpoint supports these lessons as age-appropriate tools to help children understand diversity, empathy, and human rights, arguing that gender can be complex rather than strictly binary. Conversely, many parents and educators express concern that early instruction might confuse developing minds, lack sufficient parental oversight, or encourage anxiety and confusion for young students. Ultimately, balancing these perspectives often involves schools seeking community input, while parents must navigate these challenges based on their own afterschool or home boundaries.",
